<figureCitation box="[308,417,1374,1396]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1337,1361]" captionTargetBox="[157,1433,184,1312]" captionTargetId="figure-26@13.[151,1436,181,1313]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Habitus of species of Sodalia, males (left) and females (right). 1–4. S. sodalis, 1–2. Male from Santo Antônio do Tauá, Pará, Brazil (DZ 35.537), 3–4. Female from Cacaulândia, Rôndonia, Brazil (OM 21.494). 5–8. S. argyrospila, 5–6. Male from Antonina, Paraná, Brazil (OM 14.223), 7–8. Female from Pontal do Paraná, Paraná, Brazil (OM 25.358). 9–12. S. coler, 9–10. Male from Pontal do Paraná, Paraná, Brazil (DZ 35.842), 11–12. Female from Seara, Santa Catarina, Brazil (DZ 35.696). 13–16. S. petiti sp. nov., 13–14. Male holotype from Alluriquin, Ecuador (OM 52.619). 15–16. Female allotype from Alluriguin, Ecuador (DZ 31.487). 17–18. S. spangla comb. nov., male from Oso Perdido, Amazonas, Peru (OM 83.945). Scale bar: 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423891/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">Figs 17–18</figureCitation>
